// @test regression/field-on-non-udt
// @description A scalar value has no fields, so a member read like `close.foo` is TV's CE10198 "Object has no field foo". Valid member access stays clean: namespace members (color.red, math.pi), and UDT field reads (pt.x). Restricted to a plain Identifier receiver so deep-namespace members (strategy.commission.*) are untouched. Probed 2026-06-25 via pine-lint --tv, see INV093.
// @expects parse: success
// @expects error: line=3, message=/Object has no field foo/
// @expects errors: 1

//@version=6
indicator("field-on-non-udt")
y = close.foo
c = color.red
p = math.pi
type Pt
    float x
pt = Pt.new()
v = pt.x
plot(p + v, color = c)
